
[1]armed

   'ARMED, pp.

   1. Furnished with weapons of offense or defense; furnished with the
   means of security; fortified, in a moral sense.

   2. In heraldry, armed is when the beaks, talons, horns, or teeth of
   beasts and birds of prey are of a different color from the rest of the
   body.

   3. Capped and cased as the load stone; that is set in iron.

   An armed ship is one which is taken into the service of government for
   a particular occasion, and armed like a ship of war.
